Recognize the importance of prayer (spoken, sung, spontaneous, rote,
etc.) and God's Word in one's life

5EF6E72E06D54C038E7E676A0D929D5A.description:
We Pray- prayer is an essential
way we respond to God who loved
us first. Prayer is necessary if we
are to know God personally and to
do His will. Living the Christian life
is only possible with the help of
prayer.

C12964DA8F4943D088FF4054C9B460A7.description:
Understand that God gives us rules to teach us how to love God and
others

004EEAE8B3AE4CF18D2F3484642C992F.description: Discuss appropriate ways to express sorrow, anger, happiness and love

A89E0D2ED5F147D4B7D27BDD7F716FCE.description: Discuss the virtues as habits of appropriate behavior

6F2AD8719E24498F8DC56F7BC711E170.description: Develop a sense of right and wrong behavior

6D9BCA0557F7468696D433E8D3DF46A3.description: Understand that God loves us and is always ready to forgive us.

8C001741B9A34088BC9A5C91A039E67F.description: Demonstrate respect for the world and all living things

B699976C2CDB485496B17F2D005F8D0A.description: Exhibit the ability to share, care for, love and forgive others

F2675E4C2A66436F8C7752A7F3E66A12.description:
Identify own feelings and emotions and how to express them in a
developmentally appropriate manner

191502CE99CC40CA81B546A91BD42CCC.description: Discuss that each person has feelings

BBE537F2F2CB4FC496E74D06A24FAAE5.description: Discuss that he/she belongs to a human family and God's family

B4C8A734BE1444D09490C74BCCCD3ABA.description:
Recognize that they are special to God and God wants them to be the
best person they can be

8609DA74BD0E4BE0AA75AB85658EA799.description:
We Live- Life in Christ is about
how we should respond to Jesus'
love by the way we live. As his
brothers and sisters, we should
love as he has asked. The moral
life is not an arbitrary list of rules,
but laws of love that help us to
know how to live and stay close to
Jesus. Living life as Jesus asks us
to leads to true joy and peace

63D0D71E97A7425690F67AC2D99598AD.description: Recognize that Jesus is with us in a special way at Mass

68FC899442F3451985FBA7E6800D5030.description:
Experience signs, symbols, and sacramentals of the Church (ex. Sign of
the Cross, genuflecting, kneeling, bowing, tabernacle, blessing with holy
water)

DB570FB8FEF441948519DE206C9971B7.description:
Participate in faith experiences such as prayer services in the classroom
and/or in church. Mass participation may be included where appropriate

3C39BB3CB7424C929C99B7A501C06C83.description:
We Worship- This section pertains
to the way God continues to make
available to us His grace won for
us by Jesus' saving Death and
Resurrection. We receive God's
saving grace in the sacraments
which are actions of God to bring
us into communion with Him and
to strengthen us to remain in
communion with Him. He has
given us a share in His divine life for no other reason than He loves
us. We need to respond to the
grace God gives us in the
Sacraments.

0B5EA26CD38F4B5E9D735C5419E641D1.description: Identify Mary as the Mother of Jesus (the Second Person of the Trinity).

0A30F62D8A644E96811CB529A1EEB0E8.description: Build an awareness of the Church as the family of God

D30172DB37E84A96A6F857DAA5C97FAE.description:
Identify the family as the Church at home and begin to understand the
special role families have in sharing the faith of the Church.

1C5E9568AA16447ABC60B5E13E743708.description:
Identify the priest (and religious sisters and brothers) and begin to
understand their special roles in the local church.

3BF076AC23AE46A4BB38D38EFD356A06.description:
Identify the patron saint of the school or the event after which the church
is named

529C9C58E54F4B219FF07B1C6C54AD00.description: Identify Jesus as a role model for loving God and other people

8D778C5940974CF5A8C4E7B02A3F51C8.description: Recognize Jesus as friend and teacher

3691CB1711A5457696DD04B52A2EE072.description:
Recognize that Jesus is in his/her heart (parable of the mustard seed,
the Good Shepherd, the hidden treasures)

8F8BC0E76EBA4B7D90FF497324078794.description: Recognize that all God's creation is good

9AD33DED012E4A0FBFD94EAC03C9CDC2.description: Acknowledge that everything/everyone is created by God

E4441DC640AF473EB830BE00B1074913.description: Develop practices to build an ongoing relationship with our Loving God

F2DD1CCD6A3C4208A59C11214E68A7AD.description:
We Believe- The Creed pertains to
what God, our Heavenly Father
has revealed about Himself and
His plan for our salvation (saving
us from sin) and sanctification
(making us holy) through Jesus
Christ His Son by the power of the
Holy Spirit. God has acted first.
Faith is our response to what God
has revealed. These Truths are
gathered together in the Creed
